/public/docs/guild/mage/nonmage
=======================

So, you're interested in the ways of the magi... a wise decision.  Magi have
the ability to do the most direct damage of any guild in Darkwind.  While
we do not wear heavy armor or wield large weapons other than staves, our
spells more than make up for it in time of need.  Of course, magi also have
a variety of utility spells for use in non-combat situations.

The magi are ranked in power by their Guild Level (GL).  The GL 1 magi is
just learning the crafts of summoning light and casting magic missiles, while
the GL 15 mage can bring the touch of death itself against an opponent.  Of
course, in the hands of a GL 15 mage, even the meager magic missile can do
tremendous damage...

Combat Spells
=============
As mentioned above, as the magi increase in guild level, they increase in
firepower.  I've listed the various attack spells below as well as the guild
level when they are acquired.  The spell point cost refers to the cost when
the mage has just learned the skill; as the mage increases in ability, the
cost increases, as does the destructive potential of the spell.

     Magic Missile  - GL 1 -  7 SP
     Fireball       - GL 3 - 10 SP
     Icestorm       - GL 4 - 15 SP (attacks multiple creatures at once!)
     Wrath          - GL 7 - 50 SP
     Touch of Death - GL 15 (and Normal Level 18) - 150 SP & 50 HP!

Now, magi sometimes find themselves in actual physical combat.  While this
is not our forte, we have spells which can help us in this endeavor as well,
providing both physical protection from weapons and increasing our resistance
to enemy spells.

     Armor  - GL 5 -  75 SP
     Negate - GL 9 - 100 SP

Non-Combat Spells
=================

An adventurer's life consists of more than combat, and so does the mage's
repetoire of spells.  Magi can see into remote locations, determine secret
information concerning an object, and teleport objects to other players.  A
more complete list of abilities follows:

     Find (GL 1) - Locate other people
     Illuminate (GL 1) - Create light
     Detect (GL 2) - Detect evil monsters
     Analyze (GL 2) - Identify objects
     Insanity (GL 4) - Great ice-breaker at parties!
     Magic Eye (GL 6) - Spies into an adjacent room
     Blink (GL 8) - Teleports the mage to another location 
     Darkwind/Souvrael (GL 9) - Teleports a person to Darkwind/Souvrael
     Gate (GL 11) - Teleports an object to another player
     Powerup (GL 13) - Converts hit points into spell points

The Life of the Magi
====================

Magi are inherently good, so they may not cast spells if they have an
evil alignment.  Intelligence is of primary importance in spell casting,
so a prospective mage must have an intelligence of at least 6 in order to
join the guild.  Finally, the magi form a close fellowship, able to
communicate with each other regardless of physical location.

While this is a good introduction, the best way to find out about the life
of a magi is to ask one!  We will be glad to show you why the magi form the
best guild in Darkwind!
